i## Creating Open5GS Configuration Files		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIf you are using Ubuntu, the above installation process should have		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iautomatically installed the default configuration files to `/etc/freeDiameter`		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iand `/etc/open5gs` . However, in NixOS, this process is not automatic,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iand we need to manually copy the configuration files or manually		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ispecify their paths.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iSince the Nixpkgs Open5GS package already comes with a set of default		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iconfigurations, we can directly copy the default configuration files		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifrom this package. First, build the package:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  nix build nixpkgs#open5gs		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIf all goes well, Nix will download the pre-compiled Open5GS from the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iBinary Cache and symlink it to the `result` directory. At this point,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iwe can see the default configuration files in the `result/etc` folder:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  ls result/etc		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThen we can copy them to our NixOS configuration for later		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
imodification:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  cp -r result/etc/freeDiameter /path/to/your/nixos-config/freeDiameter		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  cp -r result/etc/open5gs /path/to/your/nixos-config/open5gs		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Files copied from Nix store are read-only by default, add write permissions to them		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  chmod -R +w /path/to/your/nixos-config/freeDiameter /path/to/your/nixos-config/open5gs		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iFor files in the `freeDiameter` folder, we need to place them under `/etc/freeDiameter` :		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    environment.etc."freeDiameter".source = ./freeDiameter;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  }		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iFor files in the `open5gs` folder, you can directly specify the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iconfiguration file path using the `-c` parameter when starting		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iOpen5GS:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    systemd.services = {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      # ...		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      ExecStart = "${pkgs.open5gs}/bin/open5gs-${svc}d -c ${./open5gs}/${svc}.yaml";		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      # ...		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    };		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  }		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
